node.text: Here we go again…um, again. This past month has seen seemingly endless swell in the South Pacific, and specifically, at Puerto Escondido — from a two-day bender a few weeks back, to another round earlier this week. And here's the #CamRewind highlights from the most recent pulse; hit the link in bio to watch Puerto Escondido live.

node.title: Yet Another Round of South Swell at Puerto Escondido

node.text:
Last year, @jacksatariano and friends ventured down to Mexico for the first annual Surfline Spirit of Surfing Cuervo Challenge. But unfortunately, his entry wasn’t picked for the grand prize, private session at Surf Ranch. No worries, though, because Jack’s back this year for a shot at the golden ticket with a romp around his favorite spots in SoCal. And he did so accordingly on National Tequila Day. | @josecuervotequila 
 
We want to say thanks to everyone that submitted entries! Public voting ends tonight at midnight. Who’s going to Surf Ranch? Vote now for your favorite entries through the link in bio.

node.text:
Strapped with his arsenal of legos, a yoga mat tube simulator, and a hearty imagination, Max Montgomery (@tothemax2) depicts what the majority of us have experienced more times than we’d like to admit – a so-so surf session. But aside from his ingenious editing, what stood out most was Max’s passion for, as he said, “Helping those who often don’t get the chance to surf.”
 
Hit the link in bio to view all entries from the Surfline Spirit of Surfing Cuervo Challenge (@josecuervotequila) and vote for your favorite. Note: entry submission deadline ends on 11:59 p.m. PT Sunday, July 25th, so there’s still time to submit your video and secure your chance for a dream session at Surf Ranch with Gerry Lopez.

node.text:
Two incredibly deep, incredibly long tubes from the Mentawais during the recent run of swell in Indo. First up, Gabriel Pastori (@gabrielpastori); followed by, Icaro Ronchi (@icaroronchi). "Perfect, eight-foot barrels, all day long, with offshore wind on a beautiful, sunny day with no one around," said Gabriel. "It was real, Good-to-Epic conditions!” And there’s more where that came from. Hit the link in bio to see the full #SwellStory.
🎥: @siboncharters

node.title: Biggest Swell of the Season (So Far) Hits Indonesia

node.text: The @JoseCuervotequila Spirit of Surfing Challenge is back, and the entries are flowing in. Like this one from Jennifer Ziemba (@surfvideoproductions) and, along with her recipe for the “Carve Crave” (juniper-infused tequila, anyone?), she shared clips from the past year. "Amazingly all the clips and my drone footage is from 2020 and 2021,” said Ziemba. “I surfed a lot during the pandemic.” Will she win for an exclusive session at the Surf Ranch with Gerry Lopez? You decide. Public voting is open now, live on the site.

node.text: When the tradewinds blow, sometimes they blow in the right direction. Add the words “30 knots” to that, and you get what unveiled itself along the Gold Coast and northern NSW on July 4th. Oh yeah, it was offshore too, for the first time in a week. The whole east coast of Australia was (and still is) pumping, but these five Kirra bombs captured by @shaggamang on July 4th sum up the energy and stoke of the swell as it peaked. Watch here as @hammosurfboards, @dingomorrison, @dimity, @mfanno and @josh_kerr84 take full advantage of the conditions.

node.text: Listening to Greg Noll (@nollsurfboards) describe his harrowing 1964 outer reef experience, a vanguard charge far beyond Pipeline’s breakers, his words aren’t the only thing that grab you. All those dates and distances and sizes and numbers become mere minutiae in the overall delivery of one of surfing’s most animated and gregarious legends. From the body language and hand gestures to the expletives and sound effects, Noll becomes absolutely possessed by his memories. Which makes it all so believable. Complete his reflection with Bud Browne’s classic archival footage, and you’ve got something truly extraordinary. Link in bio for the full Talk Story with Greg Noll.

node.title: Talk Story: Greg Noll, Early North Shore Exploits

Yeah, Wedge is one of the more temperamental surf spots on Planet Earth, dishing out pleasure and pain in equal parts, with no regard for social status or board choice or zip code. (OK, to be fair, maybe it leans a little heavier on the pain side. But hey.) And when the forecast long-period south swell reared its head this morning, there was plenty of both — here’s a classic example of ecstasy and agony, all in less that two minutes. #labombaswell 
First surfer: @danielsup 🎥: @evo_n8

node.text: You’ve only got one chance. One chance to take a pure, white, shaped blank and turn it into a piece of art. Once you pour hardener into those cups of colored resin, there’s no turning back. Because that resin’s gonna go off immediately -- the difference between a masterpiece and a mess hinging on every pass of the squeegee. And these four artists wouldn’t have it any other way. Watch the full edit of Resin and Soul Part III through the link in bio. | Presented by @dragonalliance.
